This paper is about a novel optimization strategy for training neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the regularization of neural networks using bit constraints, which is a technique that can be applied to a variety of neural network architectures and applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
